       <statement>Steps in Radiometric Terrain Correction of Sentinel-1 Data using Sentinel-1 Toolbox (S1TBX):
1. Download and apply precision orbit information
2. Apply calibration parameters
3. Apply speckle filtering
4. Multi-look dataset. For GRD 30-meter product, 3 x 3 looks are used.
5. Apply radiometric terrain flattening
6. Apply terrain correction
7. Post processing creates GeoTIFF files</statement>
